How to Install:

###########
# on UNIX #
###########

1) Be sure you have installed the last version of CMAKE (2.6) and the library GtkMM
2) Create a directory called "build" into .
3) Go to the new "build" directory
4) Type the following command: cmake ..
5) Use the Makefile to generate binary with the command: make
6) A binary has been normally generated into "build" called "ceg"

####################
# on Windows/MinGW #
####################

1) Install CMake for Windows: http://cmake.org/cmake/resources/software.html and add the CMake path in the PATH environment variable,
2) Install MinGW (GCC) Compiler Suite, look at the following address http://www.mingw.org/wiki/HOWTO_Install_the_MinGW_GCC_Compiler_Suite
3) Install GtkMM, http://live.gnome.org/gtkmm/MSWindows
(4)) For commiters, install SVN from http://subversion.tigris.org/servlets/ProjectDocumentList?folderID=8100
5) Create a directory called "build" into .
6) Go to the new "build" directory
7) Type the following command: cmake -G "MinGW Makefiles" ..
8) Use the Makefile to generate binary with the command: mingw32-make
9) A binary has been normally generated into "build" called "ceg"
